WEBVTT

00:10.594 --> 00:11.929
♪ You could do it solo ♪

00:11.929 --> 00:13.889
♪ But then you'd be all by yourself ♪

00:13.889 --> 00:16.433
♪ Yo! So it'd be more fun
To share this one ♪

00:16.433 --> 00:17.976
♪ With someone else ♪

00:17.976 --> 00:21.688
♪ Together we will soar
Across the sky and beyond ♪

00:21.688 --> 00:23.065
♪ So turn up your voice ♪

00:23.774 --> 00:25.567
♪ Stand up and sing along ♪

00:25.567 --> 00:26.860
♪ All different voices ♪

00:26.860 --> 00:27.861
♪ Everybody now! ♪

00:27.861 --> 00:29.404
♪ Our melodies ringing ♪

00:29.404 --> 00:31.323
♪ We're livin' in harmony ♪

00:31.323 --> 00:33.283
♪ Yeah, we're livin' in harmony ♪

00:33.283 --> 00:36.995
♪ Our song is much stronger
With every Troll singing ♪

00:36.995 --> 00:39.414
♪ We're livin' in harmony ♪♪

00:40.958 --> 00:42.918
♪

00:44.336 --> 00:47.756
POPPY: Fellow Trolls,
I'm thrilled to officially open

00:47.756 --> 00:51.593
the first ever TrollsTopia
Community Garden!

00:52.469 --> 00:54.721
[ cheering ]

00:54.721 --> 00:57.683
Now there's a place for Trolls
to garden together,

00:57.683 --> 01:01.311
allowing us to explore
the agricultural styles

01:01.311 --> 01:05.941
of all the Tribes, side by side,
in perfect plant‐based harmony!

01:06.233 --> 01:07.192
Woo!

01:08.652 --> 01:09.486
ALL:
Huh?

01:10.279 --> 01:14.366
‐ Sorry, sometimes when I'm this excited,
I cut an extra red ribbon.

01:14.658 --> 01:17.244
‐ Uh‐huh.
‐ I get it.

01:17.452 --> 01:19.663
‐ Now let's get gardening!

01:19.663 --> 01:21.540
BIGGIE:
Wait for me! Wait for me!

01:21.540 --> 01:24.543
‐ Haha! what up, Poppy?

01:24.918 --> 01:26.503
‐ Hey!
‐ Hey!

01:26.503 --> 01:28.088
‐ Hey!

01:28.088 --> 01:29.840
‐ But seriously, we have a problem.

01:30.424 --> 01:32.759
‐ Oh! You do?
‐ LAGUNA: Indeed.

01:32.759 --> 01:36.096
You see, our tribe would love
to contribute to the garden,

01:36.096 --> 01:39.891
but indigenous Techno foliage
has heretofore only grown underwater.

01:39.891 --> 01:42.728
We have no idea
how they would fare on dry land.

01:42.728 --> 01:44.771
‐ Oh. That's a tough one...

01:45.147 --> 01:47.149
Hmm...

01:47.983 --> 01:51.486
Sorry, sometimes when I feel conflicted,
I cut a gray ribbon.

01:51.945 --> 01:54.031
‐ Uh, yeah. We get it.

01:54.364 --> 01:55.782
‐ It was already quite clear.

01:56.283 --> 01:58.952
‐ Laguna, Synth,
I totally get the dilemma.

01:59.244 --> 02:02.914
But we can't have a TrollsTopian garden
without the Techno Trolls.

02:02.914 --> 02:06.126
So, could you try
planting something on dry land?

02:07.377 --> 02:10.213
‐ Well, I suppose we could subvert

02:10.213 --> 02:13.550
thousands of years of evolution
and roll the dice?

02:13.925 --> 02:16.386
‐ Yay! I'm so relieved...

02:16.386 --> 02:17.888
Ah...

02:19.806 --> 02:23.352
Sorry, sometimes when I feel relieved,
I cut a blue ribbon.

02:23.352 --> 02:24.645
‐ We get it.
‐ We get it.

02:25.604 --> 02:28.106
[ humming ]

02:28.106 --> 02:31.360
‐ Hey! Lovin' the orchestral orchids!

02:31.360 --> 02:33.487
♪

02:33.487 --> 02:35.864
Beautiful laugh‐o‐dills!

02:35.864 --> 02:38.742
[ laughing ]

02:38.742 --> 02:42.120
Oh. And that weeping willow is so lovely,

02:42.746 --> 02:43.955
it's downright moving.

02:44.414 --> 02:48.251
‐ Now, don't you start cryin'
or I'll start cryin' and...

02:48.251 --> 02:50.712
Yep, there I go!

02:53.799 --> 02:57.427
‐ What's up, Val?
Watering those "Hard Rock Hedges"?

02:57.803 --> 03:00.597
‐ Uh, no.
You don't water Hard Rock Hedges.

03:00.597 --> 03:04.351
♪

03:05.018 --> 03:07.187
‐ Ooh. Implausible.

03:08.021 --> 03:11.608
‐ Say hello to the Funk Fruit Bush, baby.

03:11.817 --> 03:16.154
A tasty fruit that packs
an extra funky surprise...

03:16.488 --> 03:19.074
[ Lownote voice ]
‐ What's the surprise? Oh!

03:19.074 --> 03:22.869
Never mind, I get it now, baby.

03:22.869 --> 03:25.288
[ laughing ]

03:25.539 --> 03:27.290
[ normal voice ]
So, Laguna, Synth,

03:27.582 --> 03:30.001
I gotta ask,
how's the Techno garden doing?

03:30.252 --> 03:31.586
‐ Well, Poppy,

03:31.586 --> 03:34.840
this is one of our Dance Plants
under normal conditions.

03:36.758 --> 03:41.221
‐ But on dry land,
they're growing way bigger!

03:42.889 --> 03:43.932
‐ What?

03:43.932 --> 03:48.562
‐ Yes. It appears the direct sunlight
has caused the plants to thrive.

03:48.562 --> 03:49.855
‐ Yes!

03:49.855 --> 03:53.567
Haha! Well, that seals it.
It is now safe to say

03:53.567 --> 03:57.571
that the TrollsTopia Community Garden
is a huge success!

03:58.071 --> 03:59.406
‐ Mr. Dinkles, no!

04:02.117 --> 04:04.828
‐ Ah! He's eating our Techno Plants!

04:04.828 --> 04:08.039
‐ Mr. Dinkles is Techniverous!

04:08.248 --> 04:11.084
‐ Dinkles, stop!
You're ruining the garden!

04:12.085 --> 04:14.546
I'm so sorry, everyone!

04:14.546 --> 04:17.007
But I promise he won't do it agai‐‐

04:17.007 --> 04:19.342
[ Mr. Dinkles munches ]

04:19.342 --> 04:21.136
Ah, Mr. Dinkles! No!

04:23.305 --> 04:24.890
Phew, there!

04:25.223 --> 04:26.224
‐ Uh, Biggie?

04:28.059 --> 04:30.896
‐ Gah!
‐ Whoa, whoa, whoa, easy, Biggie.

04:30.896 --> 04:32.814
There's gotta be something we can do

04:32.814 --> 04:35.233
to stop Mr. Dinkles
from eating the Dance Plants.

04:35.233 --> 04:40.530
‐ Well, to keep a critter out of the crops
back in Lonesome Flats, we'd put up...

04:41.072 --> 04:42.824
a scareTroll.

04:43.617 --> 04:44.826
‐ What's a scareTroll?

04:45.076 --> 04:46.495
‐ It's a scarecrow...

04:46.870 --> 04:48.997
but with the word Troll in it.

04:49.831 --> 04:51.458
‐ Oh.
‐ Oh.

04:51.958 --> 04:53.543
‐ Only question is,

04:53.668 --> 04:57.130
what kind of scareTroll
would keep Mr. Dinkles away?

04:57.380 --> 04:59.090
And for that we need...

04:59.549 --> 05:03.637
a scareTroll fashion show, ya'll!

05:03.637 --> 05:07.933
♪

05:07.933 --> 05:09.059
Aw.

05:09.059 --> 05:09.976
Ah!

05:09.976 --> 05:16.024
♪ Well, ya looking real good
Like I knew you would today ♪

05:17.442 --> 05:19.569
♪ Darlin', oh, if you want ♪

05:19.569 --> 05:24.282
♪ You can try it all on and see, yeah ♪

05:24.825 --> 05:26.701
♪ What's gonna work for you ♪

05:26.701 --> 05:28.453
♪ Try on a thing or two ♪

05:28.453 --> 05:31.748
♪ Show me your stuff
Work it, work it for me ♪

05:32.165 --> 05:34.334
♪ We'll find the perfect lo... ♪

05:34.334 --> 05:35.585
BIGGIE:
Excuse me, Guy?

05:35.877 --> 05:37.420
What's scary about that one?

05:37.712 --> 05:39.548
‐ He's wearing horizontal stripes!

05:39.840 --> 05:42.926
From a fashion perspective,
it's terrifying!

05:43.635 --> 05:47.138
♪ We'll do it all, work it,
work it for me ♪

05:47.138 --> 05:49.349
♪ Yeah ♪♪

05:49.349 --> 05:51.768
‐ You know,
'cuz fish eat worms and what not!

05:53.687 --> 05:59.734
♪

06:02.612 --> 06:06.741
‐ Haha! It works, gang!
We saved the garden!

06:06.741 --> 06:09.160
[ cheering ]

06:09.160 --> 06:10.620
It's like I always say,

06:10.620 --> 06:12.831
when you really put
your mind to something,

06:12.831 --> 06:14.916
you can overcome any obstacle!

06:15.208 --> 06:17.377
<i>You can overcome any obstacle...</i>

06:17.669 --> 06:18.837
<i>Any obstacle...</i>

06:18.837 --> 06:20.463
FISH SCARECROW:
Any obstacle.

06:21.131 --> 06:22.257
[ Mr. Dinkles munches ]

06:22.799 --> 06:24.134
‐ Mr. Dinkles, no!

06:26.595 --> 06:27.429
‐ Ah!
‐ Ah!

06:27.637 --> 06:32.100
‐ B‐but how?
I thought the scareTroll scared him.

06:32.350 --> 06:33.184
‐ Mew.

06:36.396 --> 06:38.440
‐ Mh, yeah. He says it did,

06:38.440 --> 06:42.444
but your speech inspired him
to face his fears.

06:42.736 --> 06:44.613
‐ Aww, way to go, Dinkles.

06:45.030 --> 06:46.698
But also... frosting!

06:46.698 --> 06:49.326
♪

06:49.326 --> 06:51.661
‐ You know,
when we were little funk Trolls,

06:51.661 --> 06:53.371
we were always sneaking cookies

06:53.371 --> 06:56.666
from our ship's baked
confection stasis container.

06:56.666 --> 06:58.668
‐ Or what you would call a "cookie jar."

06:58.918 --> 07:02.797
‐ So, to teach us a lesson,
our parents let us eat so many cookies

07:02.797 --> 07:06.509
that we got an awful case
of interstellar queezears.

07:06.509 --> 07:08.428
‐ Or what you would call a "tummy ache."

07:08.887 --> 07:13.350
‐ After that,
we never wanted to eat cookies again.

07:14.434 --> 07:15.393
‐ Hm...
‐ Hm...

07:16.895 --> 07:19.564
[ beeping sound ]

07:21.399 --> 07:23.234
‐ Okay. Here goes nothing...

07:37.040 --> 07:37.916
[ gasp ]

07:42.837 --> 07:43.713
‐ Mew.

07:44.172 --> 07:48.468
‐ Mr. Dinkles says he never wants to eat
another dance plant again.

07:48.802 --> 07:52.180
[ cheering ]

07:52.555 --> 07:54.599
‐ Well, problem solved, Trolls.

07:54.599 --> 07:56.893
I think it is now safe to say

07:56.893 --> 08:01.272
that the TrollsTopia Community Garden
is a huge, huge...

08:01.815 --> 08:02.941
Huge!

08:02.941 --> 08:06.319
♪

08:06.319 --> 08:08.405
‐ Hold up!
Is it me, or are the dance plants

08:08.405 --> 08:09.823
like super big now, yo?

08:10.073 --> 08:14.911
‐ Super big?
Well, that's, that's a good thing, right?

08:14.911 --> 08:20.917
[ crackling ]

08:21.292 --> 08:26.506
♪

08:26.506 --> 08:27.632
[ Poppy screams ]

08:27.632 --> 08:30.176
It's dancing this way! Run!

08:30.176 --> 08:34.973
[ screaming ]

08:36.433 --> 08:37.642
[ screaming ]

08:37.642 --> 08:38.601
‐ Huh?
‐ Huh?

08:38.601 --> 08:42.147
[ screaming ]

08:43.898 --> 08:45.859
[ panting ]

08:45.859 --> 08:47.235
‐ Have no fear!

08:47.235 --> 08:52.198
I will communicate with the plant
through the universal language of dance.

08:53.116 --> 08:53.950
Wait.

08:54.826 --> 08:56.995
The universal language is math!

08:57.287 --> 08:58.246
Oh!

08:58.538 --> 09:00.582
[ Cooper laughs ]

09:01.708 --> 09:02.542
[ gasp ]

09:07.213 --> 09:11.217
‐ Aw. W‐We can't stop it,
it's just too strong.

09:11.217 --> 09:12.052
DINKLES:
Mew.

09:12.343 --> 09:13.178
‐ Huh?
‐ Huh?

09:14.179 --> 09:15.305
[ groaning ]

09:16.097 --> 09:16.931
‐ Mew.

09:17.223 --> 09:19.726
‐ He says, "Yes, I know."

09:20.769 --> 09:22.062
‐ Mr. Dinkles?

09:22.062 --> 09:24.522
This is why you were eating
the dance plants?

09:24.522 --> 09:26.441
Because you were trying to protect us?

09:27.150 --> 09:28.068
‐ Mew.

09:28.068 --> 09:31.112
‐ He says, "Yes. But don't be afraid.

09:31.404 --> 09:33.239
I won't let anything happen to you,

09:33.782 --> 09:35.200
not on my watch."

09:38.661 --> 09:41.247
‐ But, Mr. Dinkles,
how could you possibly?

09:41.247 --> 09:42.916
We fed you too many dance plants!

09:43.583 --> 09:44.375
‐ Mew.

09:44.709 --> 09:47.629
‐ He then goes on to say,
"Be that as it may,

09:47.629 --> 09:51.508
in times of great peril a hero must rise.

09:51.508 --> 09:55.637
Maybe not the hero you deserve.
But the hero you need."

09:57.555 --> 09:59.849
‐ He's the best of all of us, yo.

10:00.475 --> 10:04.562
♪

10:04.562 --> 10:05.522
[ scream ]

10:05.522 --> 10:11.528
♪

10:44.144 --> 10:45.436
LAGUNA:
He did it!

10:45.436 --> 10:51.359
Restored to their underwater environment,
the plants have returned to normal!

10:51.359 --> 10:52.402
‐ Yay!
‐ Yay!

10:52.986 --> 10:56.489
‐ Hm. As disappointing
as it will be, Poppy.

10:56.489 --> 11:00.326
Perhaps, given the mayhem,
it's best that we Techno Trolls

11:00.326 --> 11:02.745
abstain from the community garden.

11:03.288 --> 11:05.790
‐ No! There has to be some way...

11:06.166 --> 11:07.000
‐ Mew.

11:07.542 --> 11:10.170
‐ He says, "Why not just dig a pond?"

11:12.922 --> 11:18.928
♪

11:18.928 --> 11:19.762
‐ There.

11:20.138 --> 11:25.768
Now the TrollsTopia Community Garden
truly represents all the tribes.

11:26.060 --> 11:28.855
[ cheering ]

11:29.522 --> 11:32.567
Sorry, sometimes when a problem
has been resolved,

11:32.567 --> 11:34.027
I cut a purple ribbon.

11:34.027 --> 11:35.528
‐ We know!
‐ We know!

11:36.237 --> 11:37.071
‐ Hehe.

11:40.116 --> 11:42.118
♪

11:44.454 --> 11:46.080
R:
<i>Eighty‐seven holes...</i>

11:47.040 --> 11:50.001
<i>All on a sprawling, pristine landscape...</i>

11:50.960 --> 11:54.047
B:
<i>How can one mini‐golf course hold so much?</i>

11:54.797 --> 11:56.799
‐ 'Cuz it's super‐duper tiny, ya'll!

11:58.218 --> 12:01.930
‐ It's our latest invention:
Mini mini‐golf!

12:01.930 --> 12:04.766
‐ Mini golf so mini
you need a shrink ray to play!

12:05.183 --> 12:06.726
‐ We also invented a shrink ray.

12:08.102 --> 12:09.854
‐ Ooh!
‐ Ooh!

12:10.063 --> 12:13.775
‐ So, find a golf buddy
and prepare to get your shrink on!

12:14.108 --> 12:16.027
[ cheering ]

12:16.027 --> 12:20.073
‐ Oh! 'Tis been far too long
since I've "hit the links."

12:20.073 --> 12:21.074
[ chuckle ]

12:21.074 --> 12:24.369
I shall summon my own personal clubs.

12:24.369 --> 12:28.623
♪

12:28.623 --> 12:30.959
‐ Whoa, Dante!

12:30.959 --> 12:32.543
You just wave that stick thing

12:32.543 --> 12:36.339
and a buncha little dudes float around,
singin' and givin' you golf stuff?

12:36.798 --> 12:37.882
Ha!

12:37.882 --> 12:39.217
That is so...

12:39.217 --> 12:41.344
[ imitates airhorn ]

12:41.344 --> 12:44.222
[ imitates birds sounds ]

12:44.222 --> 12:45.932
[ barking ]

12:45.932 --> 12:47.976
‐ What? What is happening?

12:48.518 --> 12:49.644
‐ "What is happening?"

12:50.770 --> 12:52.772
You are funny, bro!

12:52.772 --> 12:53.606
‐ Oh!

12:54.274 --> 12:57.026
‐ Hey, you know what?
We should be golf buddies!

12:57.026 --> 12:58.861
Ah? Heh?

12:58.861 --> 13:00.530
‐ Golf buddies? You and me?

13:01.072 --> 13:02.448
Well, I mean, um...

13:02.448 --> 13:04.701
‐ I'll take that as a solid "Yes!"

13:04.701 --> 13:06.536
‐ Shrink ray!
‐ Shrink ray!

13:12.625 --> 13:13.751
[ whistle ]

13:13.751 --> 13:15.378
‐ Nice drive, Poppy!

13:15.378 --> 13:17.171
That ball must have gone at least...

13:17.964 --> 13:19.090
five inches!

13:21.092 --> 13:22.719
‐ Perhaps a bit more um...

13:24.679 --> 13:25.888
Or is it...

13:29.434 --> 13:30.643
‐ Mmhmm...

13:32.353 --> 13:33.187
[ scream ]

13:35.189 --> 13:36.107
‐ Huh?

13:36.107 --> 13:38.026
♪

13:38.026 --> 13:41.154
‐ Whoop! Sorry, D. C.,
I was lookin' at the stick thing

13:41.154 --> 13:43.197
and made the little dudes come back.

13:43.197 --> 13:44.866
Ooh! Can they dubstep?

13:45.491 --> 13:47.452
[ chuckle ]

13:47.452 --> 13:48.369
‐ Hm...

13:48.661 --> 13:51.456
Um, Poppy? I couldn't help but notice...

13:51.456 --> 13:56.127
Branch has a hilarious golf hat,
I have a hilarious golf hat,

13:56.753 --> 13:58.963
seems we're destined
to be golf buddies, mh?

13:59.380 --> 14:00.590
Please switch with me.

14:00.590 --> 14:04.969
‐ Dante, look, I get that you and Synth
haven't spent much time together.

14:04.969 --> 14:07.388
But trust me, if you give him a chance,

14:07.388 --> 14:09.724
you're gonna find
there isn't a better friend

14:09.724 --> 14:10.725
to have by your side.

14:11.184 --> 14:12.101
‐ Yes...

14:12.101 --> 14:15.146
I suppose that is
the "Trolly" thing to do...

14:15.396 --> 14:18.357
‐ Hey, nice hat, Dante!

14:18.357 --> 14:19.734
[ whistle ]

14:23.946 --> 14:25.281
‐ Oh...

14:25.740 --> 14:26.574
[ sigh ]

14:26.908 --> 14:29.577
Yes, yes, Trolly, Trolly...

14:30.912 --> 14:32.080
Confound it...

14:32.080 --> 14:34.624
My ball simply must be
around here, somewhere...

14:35.750 --> 14:36.667
‐ Hold up!

14:36.959 --> 14:38.503
Dude, look!

14:38.503 --> 14:41.798
Somebody musta dropped
a big ol' eclair on the golf course!

14:42.256 --> 14:45.635
I've never seen an eclair
that gargantuan, bro!

14:45.885 --> 14:49.347
Ah, we gotta scope out
that éclair, like, now!

14:49.680 --> 14:52.308
[ Dante screams ]

14:52.558 --> 14:55.394
‐ Ah, Synth.
T'would be a better use of our time

14:55.394 --> 14:57.271
to stay on course, would it not?

14:58.439 --> 14:59.816
‐ But the eclair!

14:59.816 --> 15:01.526
‐ I really must insist...

15:02.360 --> 15:03.402
[ chuckle ]

15:04.195 --> 15:05.404
[ chuckle ]

15:05.404 --> 15:11.410
[ screaming ]

15:13.329 --> 15:18.251
[ screaming ]

15:21.379 --> 15:23.214
‐ Okay. Truth time, bro.

15:23.798 --> 15:26.592
I've never played golf before.
Is it always like this?

15:26.801 --> 15:28.386
‐ Ah, we're lost, Synth!

15:28.553 --> 15:32.807
With no hope of returning to normal size
because no one knows where we are!

15:33.141 --> 15:37.395
‐ Oh, yeah. And we missed our chance
to see that big ol' eclair!

15:37.812 --> 15:39.147
‐ Ugh...

15:39.147 --> 15:40.356
[ crackling ]

15:45.153 --> 15:46.445
What is that?

15:46.445 --> 15:47.363
[ gasp ]

15:47.363 --> 15:49.699
‐ Sounds straight up monstrous, bro...

15:53.744 --> 15:54.787
‐ Mew.

15:54.787 --> 15:57.039
‐ Oh! Mr. Dinkles.

15:57.039 --> 15:58.624
[ laughing ]

15:58.624 --> 16:00.585
Oh! And our friends!

16:00.877 --> 16:02.837
[ laughing ]

16:03.087 --> 16:06.007
‐ Help! Down here, yo!
‐ Hello! Down here!

16:06.716 --> 16:08.676
‐ No use, bro, we're too tiny.

16:08.676 --> 16:10.261
There's only one thing to do...

16:10.887 --> 16:15.391
Call up your little dudes
to play some duh‐duh‐duh‐dubstep!

16:15.391 --> 16:16.642
‐ Wha‐wha‐what?

16:17.393 --> 16:18.311
No!

16:18.603 --> 16:19.562
‐ Huh?

16:19.562 --> 16:20.479
[ chuckle ]

16:20.479 --> 16:22.565
‐ I mean, fun as dubstep would be,

16:22.565 --> 16:25.943
let's save it for a time when
our very lives are not in jeopardy, hm?

16:26.235 --> 16:28.821
Though, here's an idea,
perhaps with direction,

16:28.821 --> 16:32.742
my "little dudes," as you call them,
could get our friends' attention.

16:33.701 --> 16:39.707
♪

16:40.166 --> 16:41.375
‐ Wait a minute...

16:41.542 --> 16:44.212
Aren't those Dante's little dude fellers?

16:45.171 --> 16:49.175
‐ Look! They're coming over!
My idea is working!

16:49.175 --> 16:52.345
♪

16:52.345 --> 16:56.974
‐ That's weird. They're making music,
but there's no Dante to be found.

16:57.350 --> 16:58.893
Which could only mean...

16:59.393 --> 17:00.895
‐ Ah?
‐ Eh? Eh?

17:01.479 --> 17:03.940
I dunno, he's off somewhere else
or something.

17:03.940 --> 17:05.441
‐ Ugh.
‐ Ugh.

17:05.441 --> 17:07.193
‐ Seems reasonable to me.

17:07.193 --> 17:08.277
‐ Mmhmm.
‐ Mmhmm.

17:08.277 --> 17:10.279
